        "title": "Architecture types to avoid",
        "intro": "<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">The wrong architecture will lead to missed business opportunities and let your competitors pass you by as you waste time and money. Every dollar and hour invested in the wrong technology today&nbsp;&nbsp;will just add to the cost and hassle of moving from that solution in the future.&nbsp;</h3>\n",
        "style": "dark",
        "colStyle": "col-lg-6",
        "items": [
            {
                "image": {
                    "url": "https://vc4test.blob.core.windows.net/blogs/monolith.png"
                },
                "title": "Monolithic Architecture",
                "text": "<p>In a monolithic solution, all components are interconnected. If any individual part needs to be updated, the whole application has to be rewritten. This slows down new features, forces you to grow your development team and greatly limits your ecommerce speed to market.</p>\n"
            },
            {
                "image": {
                    "url": "https://vc4test.blob.core.windows.net/blogs/saas.png"
                },
                "title": "SaaS Solutions",
                "text": "<p>These solutions are suitable for a very small and basic store only. They don&#39;t allow you to modify the solution based on your business needs, and you lack control over the performance, continuity and security. As your business grows, your SaaS solution won&#39;t be able to grow along with you.</p>\n"
            },
            {
                "image": {
                    "url": "https://vc4test.blob.core.windows.net/blogs/legacy.png"
                },
                "title": "Homegrown Solutions",
                "text": "<p>Legacy solutions are expensive and challenging to maintain. To truly create enterprise software, you need to create a software company within your business, causing you to lose focus. Your team can be more productive when relying on a vendor who provides a flexible platform, where custom functionality can be built on top of it.</p>\n"
            },
            {
                "image": {
                    "url": "https://vc4test.blob.core.windows.net/blogs/closedsource.png"
                },
                "title": "Closed Source",
                "text": "<p>Closed architecture makes your innovations dependent on your vendor&#39;s road maps - you can&#39;t make your system changes on your own in a rapid fashion. This makes it much harder to customize your solution, as the vendor releases functionality required for the masses, rather than personalized features for you. Its&nbsp;also a long term problem&nbsp;to find developers who are specialists in a particular type of closed software.</p>\n"
            }
